w.woothemes.com/2011/12/wordpress-in-2012/\">The results are in</a> from the <a href=\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2011/11/28/woothemes-wordpress-wishlist-survey/\">WooThemes survey</a>. Presented in a handy infographic, this year&#8217;s survey brought to life some interesting facts from the 2,000+ <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/\">WordPress</a> users who took it.</p>\n<p>Among those surveyed, 90% feel that WordPress has graduated from blog publishing tool to full-fledged CMS, 68% use WordPress for sites requiring extensive CMS functionality, 77% make money from WordPress while 31% make their living from it, and 76% find <a href=\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2011/10/23/wordpress-and-responsive-web-design/\">responsive web design</a> to be an important factor in their theme choice.</p>\n<p>While we&#8217;re on the subject of surveys, you may want to take <a href=\"http://wordpressdotorg.polldaddy.com/s/wordpress-org-site-survey\">this short 5-question survey</a> to help improve the quality of <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/\">the main WordPress.org site</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/mrWfj7803TA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 24 Dec 2011 13:00:49 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"James\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";a:9:{s:6:\"server\";s:5:\"nginx\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Wed, 11 Jan 2012 03:12:54 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:15:\"application/xml\";s:10:\"connection\";s:5:\"close\";s:4:\"vary\";s:15:\"Accept-Encoding\";s:13:\"last-